   Fernet-encrypted and never exposed outside the encrypted store,
   because leaking them grants full read/write access to a user's Zotero
   library. Any access-token response missing `userID` while still
   carrying token/secret (a realistic malformed-response shape, not a
   contrived one) writes live, usable Zotero credentials straight into
   server logs, bypassing §9.6's entire "log leak != token leak"
   threat model since this path never touches the encryption layer at
   all. Neither the specialist's COMPLETE entry nor tester's VERIFY entry
   caught this — both were otherwise careful but didn't check what
